PRELIMINARY HEARING ON THIS CASE HELD WITH CASE NUMBER 22CF403 (STATE V HURST)


9:49 AM Defendant Ryan S Boonnam appeared by video, in custody.  Defendant qualifies for PD representation. Court will proceed with the option of having the matter reheard. Officer Jared Jazdzewski is sworn and questioned by Attorney Knaapen. Testifies to being dispatched to the Walmart store regarding a fight.  Testifies to speaking with KLS who indicated that a group of people approached him to fight. Testifies to being struck in the face by defendant, Boonnam.  Witness identifies defendant Boonnam in the courtroom.   Witness identifies defendant, Hurst, in the courtroom.  

Court finds probable cause to believe that a felony was committed and that the defendant committed it. Bond is continued.
Arraignment scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 10:00 am.
